entries.title: Aroldis Chapman agrees to one-year, $3.75M deal with Royals after disappointing end to Yankees tenure: report
entries.description: The left-handed reliever agreed to terms on a one-year, $3.75 million contract with the Kansas City Royals, according to a report from MLB.com.

entries.title: GREG GUTFELD: The CDC needs to do some serious soul-searching
entries.description: Fox News host Greg Gutfeld weighs in on a report claiming the Centers for Disease Control has "suffered a sharp decline in popular trust and confidence" on "Gutfeld!"

entries.title: David Crosby's former bandmates Graham Nash, Stephen Stills lead tributes to musician: 'Incredible legacy'
entries.description: Graham Nash and Stephen Stills honored their late Crosby, Stills & Nash bandmate David Crosby after his death at the age of 81 on Thursday. Many other celebrities also paid tribute to the late singer.

entries.title: TUCKER CARLSON: Biden is the most destructive president in American history
entries.description: Tucker Carlson explains why permanent Washington is tired of President Biden's leadership following his classified documents mishap on "Tucker Carlson Tonight."

entries.title: SEAN HANNITY: Hunter Biden's proximity to classified docs is 'concerning'
entries.description: Sean Hannity reacts to new revelations in the Biden classified docs case and a source revealing that the Secret Service is ready to provide a Delaware residence visitors log in Thursday's opening monologue.

entries.title: Indiana dad of boy seen on video playing, pointing gun pleads not guilty
entries.description: The Indiana father of a young boy filmed playing with a handgun in a hallway appeared in court Thursday.

entries.title: US sending another $2.5 billion in military aid to Ukraine
entries.description: The U.S. announced another $2.5 billion in military aid for Ukraine on Thursday, bringing the total security assistance to $26.7 billion since Russia invaded.

entries.title: New York police ID suspect in cold case murder of elderly woman with help from ex-girlfriend's Netflix viewing
entries.description: The suspect believed to have killed a New York woman nearly 30 years ago was identified Thursday.

entries.title: Memphis police say burglars 'dragged' Popeyes employees across floor, demanded cash at gunpoint
entries.description: Memphis police say that two people robbed a Popeyes chicken on Jan. 15, dragging several employees on the ground and demanding for money at gunpoint.

entries.title: Boebert shares how the fight between her and Marjorie Taylor Greene went down: 'Don't be ugly'
entries.description: Rep. Lauren Boebert, R-Colo., elaborated on a news story involving an angry confrontation with Rep. Marjorie Taylor Green, R-Ga., after the first House Speaker vote.

entries.title: Massachusetts health officials detect gonorrhea strain with 'reduced response' to antibiotics
entries.description: Massachusetts health officials have detected a strain of gonorrhea that shows a reduced response to several antibiotics, a first in the United States.

entries.title: California mom Maya Millete’s family says husband charged in her murder used spellcasters, subliminal messages
entries.description: Larry Millete allegedly hired spellcasters and tried to use a subliminal message machine on his wife, who he is accused of murdering, according to testimony during a preliminary hearing.

entries.title: Experts come out of the woodwork to say mishandling classified docs 'happens all the time,' 'just accidents'
entries.description: News personalities and former government officials came out in force to claim classified documents are mishandled frequently, and that far too much is classified overall.

entries.title: Larry Elder takes aim at San Francisco’s $5 million reparations plan: ‘When do we stop?’
entries.description: TV and radio host Larry Elder is taking aim at a new proposal in San Francisco to give $5 million to longtime Black residents in the city, asking "When do we stop?"

entries.title: Texas National Guard soldier patrolling border shoots migrant after struggle: report
entries.description: A Texas National Guard soldier shot a migrant over the weekend during a struggle, according to reports.

entries.title: California storms not linked to global warming, some scientists say
entries.description: Many were quick to blame the recent winter storms that pummeled California on global warming, but a few climate scientists say that may not necessarily be the case.

entries.title: Tee Higgins looking forward to 'happy' reunion with Damar Hamlin, sharing 'laughs and giggles'
entries.description: Bengals' Tee Higgins is excited to share 'laughs and giggles' with Damar Hamlin — the Bills' safety tackled Higgins right before going into cardiac arrest.

entries.title: Missing Atlanta man identified as body found burning in woods
entries.description: Georgia authorities have identified the body found burning in the woods in December.

entries.title: Karine Jean-Pierre’s patience with reporters compared to Job of the Bible
entries.description: Jaime Harrison, chair of the Democrat National Committee, defended WH Press Sec. Karine Jean-Pierre from criticism in a tweet and compared her Job.

entries.title: NCAA violations case stalls amid Jim Harbaugh's refusal to admit he lied: report
entries.description: A possible negotiated resolution in the NCAA case involving the Michigan football program reportedly broke down when Jim Harbaugh was asked to admit he lied to investigators.

entries.title: Dallas news anchor attempts field goals after Brett Maher's debacle
entries.description: A morning news anchor in Dallas wanted to see if he can be just as successful as Brett Maher was (or wasn't) in Monday night's wild-card round matchup.

entries.title: JESSE WATTERS: CNN decided to finally show up to the party
entries.description: Jesse Watters lays out how the media is turning against the Biden family as the classified documents scandal unfolds and Hunter's business deals become known to the public on "Jesse Watters Primetime."

entries.title: Lucy Hale explains her dating 'nonnegotiables,' why she often prefers older men
entries.description: "Pretty Little Liars" alum Lucy Hale said she likes to date older men because she's looking for someone more mature than who she dated when she was in her 20s.

entries.title: Kansas police investigate antisemitic, racial and homophobic vandalism at high school
entries.description: The football stadium press box at Blue Valley High School in Overland Park, Kansas was vandalized on Monday with racial, homophobic, and antisemitic graffiti.

entries.title: Alabama police charge suspected father in 'Baby Jane Doe' cold case murder
entries.description: Alabama police arrested the father of a child, whose remains were found in 2012 in a trailer park, with murder on Tuesday after advances in DNA technology led detectives to him.

entries.title: AOC files for re-election in deep-blue New York Congressional district
entries.description: AOC filed for re-election for her New York 14th Congressional District seat on Thursday after cruising to re-election in November 2022.

entries.title: Wisconsin man indicted in forced labor case involving woman held against her will for two years
entries.description: The Department of Justice unsealed an indictment against a Wisconsin man on Thursday, alleging he forced a woman to work against her will.

entries.title: Super Bowl champion kills mountain lion with bow and arrow
entries.description: Derek Wolfe is now the king of the jungle. The former Denver Bronco and Super Bowl 50 champion detailed his experience killing a mountain lion with a bow and arrow.

entries.title: House conservative leader rips media for ‘irrational’ debt ceiling coverage, vows ‘serious fiscal reform’
entries.description: The chairman of the RSC tore into the press for its hysterical coverage of the debt ceiling, and told his members the GOP would insist on spending cuts before allowing more borrowing.

entries.title: NFL legend Joe Namath pushes for Jets to add Aaron Rodgers this offseason
entries.description: Joe Namath said he would like the New York Jets to make a big move at the quarterback position by signing Aaron Rodgers and is even willing to do his part to facilitate it.

entries.title: Tony Dungy to attend March for Life, dubbed right-wing extremist
entries.description: Hall of Fame football coach Tony Dungy will attend the March of Life in Washington, D.C., on Jan. 20, which led to him being called a right-wing extremist.

entries.title: Biden says ‘no regrets’ over classified doc handling: ‘Nothing there’
entries.description: President Biden said Thursday he had "no regrets" when asked about his mishandling of classified documents found on four separate occasions.

entries.title: Security tip: Are you making this huge Wi-Fi mistake?
entries.description: You pay good money for your internet service and nothing is more frustrating than slow internet. It’s not always your ISP’s fault. Here are common Wi-Fi mistakes.

entries.title: 'Barn find' 1979 Pontiac Firebird Trans Am driven just 37 miles up for auction
entries.description: A 1979 Pontiac Firebird Trans Am with less than 37 miles on its odometer is being auctioned at the Barrett-Jackson event in Scottsdale, Ariz., Jan. 28.

entries.title: Former 'American Idol' contestant CJ Harris' cause of death revealed
entries.description: C.J. Harris, who competed on the 13th season of "American Idol," died from a heart attack, the Walker County Coroner's office confirmed to Fox News Digital. He was 31.

entries.title: Virginia residents reject massive solar farm plan for third time over environmental concerns
entries.description: A northern Virginia county moved closer to denying a third application for a large solar farm, citing concerns over environmental and agriculture impacts.

entries.title: NHL Network, EJ Hradek ignore Ivan Provorov after saying he should 'get involved' with war -- commentary
entries.description: The NHL Network and EJ Hradek appeared to skate by some scathing remarks made toward Philadelphia Flyers defenseman Ivan Prokorov.

entries.title: Leslie Jordan's cause of death revealed
entries.description: Comedian Leslie Jordan's cause of death was "sudden cardiac dysfunction," the Los Angeles County Medical Examiner-Coroner’s office confirmed on Thursday. He was 67.

entries.title: Britney Watson case: US Marshals search for 'armed and dangerous' ex-husband wanted for Tennessee mom's murder
entries.description: U.S. Marshals are assisting in the search for Kevin Watson, the former husband of missing Britney Watson, a Tennessee mom of three, who disappeared from Jackson on Jan. 7.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin 'not above the law' following 'Rust' shooting: Prosecutors to Judge Jeanine Pirro
entries.description: Judge Jeanine Pirro speaks to Santa Fe Count District Attorney Mary Carmack-Altwies and special prosecutor Andrea Reeb about the "Rust" shooting case.

entries.title: ICE releases nearly 3,000 detained immigrants affected by accidental data leak
entries.description: ICE confirmed Thursday that has released thousands of immigrants who were affected by a data leak that published personal information of more than 6,000 last year.

entries.title: Missing Madalina Cojocari: North Carolina police ask locals to 'flood the area with her precious face'
entries.description: North Carolina authorities continue to search for missing 11-year-old Madalina Cojocari, of Cornelius. They are asking locals to ' flood the area with her precious face.'

entries.title: EXCLUSIVE: Border Patrol chief fumed at Biden admin’s handling of whipping controversy, emails show
entries.description: Border Patrol Chief Raul Ortiz pushed back at the handling of a furor over allegations that agents had whipped illegal Haitian migrants in 2021, new emails reveal.
